<subSubSection id="1D8CD678728C9B3600EE9D633D86EFCF" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" type="biology">
<paragraph id="439F1CC7E032EA98A7452530888E00C2" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="69B92881BDEA5480AA358BB300EA9097" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
As far as known, all 
<taxonomicName id="A98280C70B475FAADD5A2341A2294526" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Amastris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Amastris" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Amastris</taxonomicName>
are subsocial, with the female parent sitting atop her uncovered egg mass, which are inserted into stems of the host, and tending her nymphs after hatching (Fig. 65). Nymphal aggregations are almost always ant-attended. Ant specimens pinned under vouchers include 
<taxonomicName id="73D666619760A057BB2D854C9129AC70" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Camponotus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="018ECDE2D949FA08D5B591E74775EC69" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Crematogaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Crematogaster" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Crematogaster</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="7C57BB697B5CEF21B441DADD0348BE97" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Azteca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Azteca" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Azteca</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="53E6AC45236F67F9AB0143C30857767B" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="74644FE3A25614A6F92F8DE8425AF064" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2641C14A55BBE8D3C28F5D9335FF3CC8" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<bibRefCitation id="C996CCE7D742B53369A3A113C789DCF6" author="Broomfield, PS" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" pagination="349 - 460" title="A revision of the genus AmastrisHomopteraMembracidae." volume="33" year="1976">Broomfield (1976)</bibRefCitation>
