<taxonomicName id="95051E3014C74CDA2C7B9749FA6E6F9F" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Amastris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Amastris" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Amastris</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="1ABCD7E1BCE30DBC96D44A04971A8689" originalValue="StÃ¥l">Stal</normalizedToken>
are difficult to characterize because some species bear no distinguishing enlarged chalazae or scoli or other features and thus resemble some taxa of other 
<taxonomicName id="87B8FDEABE518619C4D4C37B22C9A7C9" lsidName="" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Smiliinae">Smiliinae</taxonomicName>
